SIMPLE: replevin
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Replevin
<hw>Re*plev"in</hw> <pr>(-?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>replevina</ets>. See <er>Replevy</er>, and cf.
<er>Plevin</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A personal
action which lies to recover possession of goods and chattle wrongfully
taken or detained. Originally, it was a remedy peculiar to cases for
wrongful distress, but it may generally now be brought in all cases of
wrongful taking or detention.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The writ by which goods and chattels are
replevied.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Replevin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Replevin
<hw>Re*plev"in</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To
replevy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Replevisable</ent>⟦br⟧
